 Uitenhage - Uitenhage police are appealing for help with information that can assist their investigations following a house robbery in Kamesh. "On Wednesday, at about 19:00, a complainant alleged that he was watching television with his girlfriend in the lounge of his house in Cacatha Street, Mandelaville in Kamesh (Uitenhage), when he heard a sound of his dogs barking outside," described police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "He said that he opened a kitchen door to investigate, and that was when two men at the doorway, one armed with firearm held him at gunpoint and forced the two occupants into the bedroom. "The suspects stole cash, a television set and a jacket before fleeing the scene on foot." The complainant sustained a bump on the forehead, after he was hit with a firearm. Sgt Nkohi said that police are urging anyone with information, that could lead to the arrest of the suspects, to contact the investigating officer, Detective Warrant Officer Mark Bodill at 083 453 5753 or Crime Stop 08600 10111. "Callers may remain anonymous and all information will be treated strictly confidential." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 